Dr Precious Moloi-Motsepe during the SDG5 breakfast at the The Hyatt Regency on December 01, 2018 in Rosebank, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Dr Precious Moloi-Motsepe has been elected as the new chancellor of the University of Cape Town. According to a statement released by the university, Moloi-Motsepe is expected to take up the position in January. “The University of Cape Town (UCT) is proud to announce that Dr Precious Moloi-Motsepe has been duly elected as the new chancellor of the university, a position that she will take up from 1 January 2020,” read the statement. READ: Motsepe sues Botswana newspaper for defamation She takes over from Graça Machel who was first elected in 1999. Dr Moloi-Motsepe is a businesswoman and philanthropist who started her career in medicine at the University of the Witwatersrand. She has worked in various public hospitals in South Africa as well as at the Medical College of Virginia in the United States.